  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">BFL Loan Project</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="2">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">(i) Increase access to credit for SMEs and individual clients in Laos where banking penetration is still very low.  (ii) Demonstration effect: this will be the second loan of IFC in a commercial bank in Laos thus far and provide a role model for commercial banks keen to strengthen their corporate governance and better serve their customers and save cost.</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The Project (BFL Loan) consists of a senior loan of up to US$15 million to be provided to the Banque Franco-Lao Ltd. (BFL or the Bank) with a up to 7-year maturity in order to support the Bank to further extend loans to the SME sector in Lao PDR.</narrative>
  </description>
